Bola Tinubu, presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), has been declared the winner of the presidential election in Ondo state. The former Lagos governor scored a total of 369,924 votes to defeat his closet rival, Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), who had 115,463 votes and Peter Obi of the Labour Party who polled 47,350 votes. More subsequentlyâ€¦